South Korean soldiers wearing protective gear spray disinfectant as part of preventive measures against the spread of the COVID-19 coronavirus. JOHANNESBURG - Football matches and other big sporting events in Italy will take place without fans present. The ban will be in place until 3 April. READ: Impact of coronavirus on Corona beer sales Schools and universities will also be closed for the next two weeks. The preventive measures are part of government's plan to contain the spread of the coronavirus. Italy has seen over a hundred deaths with more than three-thousand confirmed cases.